This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Laticia M Medina in court.  Attorney Joel H. Rosenthal in court for Laticia M Medina.  Prosecuting attorney Brad Alan Vorpahl in court for the State of Wisconsin. Deputy court clerk cmt. 
State advised the Court they have complied with the Victims' Rights Law. Court addresses agreement violation. Case adjourned for another review hearing. Branch 17.
Review hearing scheduled for November 21, 2022 at 09:45 am.
DPA Progress Report, received and filed

Defendant Laticia M Medina in court with attorney Joel H. Rosenthal.  Thomas Hasle appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  On state's motion court amended defendant's name to the correct spelling of her first name which is spelled Latesia.
*
The parties have agreed to a deferred judgment agreement. as to Counts 1 & 2.
The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, pled GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, jury instructions/elements and Addendum to Plea Questionnaire received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty but WITHHELD entry of Judgment of Conviction.  The court approved the Deferred Prosecution Agreement and ordered the case transferred to Judge Stark, Branch 17 for a review hearing.  Review hearing scheduled for October 25, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Laticia M Medina in court with attorney Joel H. Rosenthal.  Nate Kristian McClure appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Laticia M Medina appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defense has received discovery. Defendant to be TAD evaluated.   DPA Hearing scheduled in Branch 37.   All parties are advised effective August 1, 2022 this case will be assigned to a Branch of RESERVE JUDGES.  Deferred prosecution agreement hearing scheduled for August 15, 2022 at 09:00 am.

No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Laticia M Medina in court.  Jennifer L Pickett appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
